ckerman (page does not exist)\">Inon Zuckerman</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Brandon_Wilson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Brandon Wilson (page does not exist)\">Brandon Wilson</a>, <a href=\"/Dana_S._Nau\" title=\"Dana S. Nau\">Dana S. Nau</a> (<b>2018</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/coin.12162\">Avoiding game-tree pathology in 2-player adversarial search</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_Intelligence_(journal)\">Computational Intelligence</a>, Vol. 34, No. 2</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Search_Pathology&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=476965\">Theory: Deeper Search creating worse performance due to PE</a> by <a href=\"/Charles_Roberson\" title=\"Charles Roberson\">Charles Roberson</a>, January 04, 2006</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=35538\">Pathology on Game trees</a> by <a href=\"/Gerd_Isenberg\" title=\"Gerd Isenberg\">Gerd Isenberg</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 22, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58527&amp;start=10\">Re: Null Move in Quiescent search</a> by <a href=\"/Harm_Geert_Muller\" title=\"Harm Geert Muller\">Harm Geert Muller</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 10, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/Null_Move_Pruning\" title=\"Null Move Pruning\">Null Move Pruning</a>, <a href=\"/Quiescence_Search\" title=\"Quiescence Search\">Quiescence Search</a>